CONTEXT
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
MRR's approver_agent_node does direct DB queries (no LLM streaming)
and emits its response as an AIMessage via on_chain_end. The SSE
controller's static_output_nodes filter must include the node's name
for the message to reach the user.

But RMS and HRMS also have approver_agent_node nodes — these use LLM
streaming and must NOT be in static_output_nodes (would cause
duplicate output).

The fix: rename MRR's approver nodes to unique names so the filter
can include only MRR's names without affecting RMS/HRMS.

Additionally: approver_agent_node has a SQL bug — it queries
TOTALCOST but the actual column is TOTAL_COST. Fix as part of this
task.

